---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — John Smith Astrophotography">
  <section class="wrap intro">
    <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
    <h1>About</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap body">
    <p>
      I'm an amateur astrophotographer based in Glasgow, capturing deep-sky
      objects from a small back-garden setup and the occasional darker site
      when the weather and life cooperate.
    </p>
    <p>
      What pulls me back to it is the absurdity of the photons themselves —
      most of what gets recorded on the sensor over a clear night left its
      source millions of years before any human held a camera. Sit with
      anything for seven hours and the universe quietly draws itself in.
    </p>
    <p>
      For prints, collaboration, or just to talk about gear, get in touch
      via <a href="mailto:hello@example.com" class="link">email</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .intro {
    padding: 80px 0 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }
  .intro h1 { margin-top: 12px; }
  .body {
    max-width: 64ch;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 20px;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .body p { margin: 0; }
  .link {
    color: var(--text);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .link:hover { border-color: var(--text); }
</style>
